" title=\"Alexander the Great\">Alexander the Great<\/a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Genghis_Khan\" title=\"Genghis Khan\">Genghis Khan<\/a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Chandragupta_Maurya\" title=\"Chandragupta Maurya\">Chandragupta Maurya<\/a> and many\nothers.<sup class=\"reference\" id=\"cite_ref-CAL-hist_9-1\"><a href=\"#cite_note-CAL-hist-9\"><span>[<\/span>10<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup class=\"reference\" id=\"cite_ref-Galvin-PreIslamic_10-1\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Galvin-PreIslamic-10\"><span>[<\/span>11<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup>\nIt has also served as a source from which many local dynasties, for\nexample <a href=\"/wiki/Greco-Bactrian_Kingdom\" title=\"Greco-Bactrian Kingdom\">Greco-Bactrians<\/a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Kushan_Empire\" title=\"Kushan Empire\">Kushans<\/a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Hephthalite\" title=\"Hephthalite\">Hephthalites<\/a>, or\n<a href=\"/wiki/Ghaznavids\" title=\"Ghaznavids\">Ghaznavids<\/a> have\nestablished empires of their own.<sup class=\"reference\" id=\"cite_ref-13\"><a href=\"#cite_note-13\"><span>[<\/span>14<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","<p>The <a href=\"/wiki/Political_history\" title=\"Political history\">political history<\/a> of modern\nAfghanistan begins in the 18th century with the rise of the <a href=\"/wiki/Pashtun_people\" title=\"Pashtun people\">Pashtun\ntribes<\/a> (known as <em>Afghans<\/em> in <a href=\"/wiki/Persian_language\" title=\"Persian language\">Persian\nlanguage<\/a>), when in 1709 the <a href=\"/wiki/Hotaki_dynasty\" title=\"Hotaki dynasty\">Hotaki dynasty<\/a> rose to power in <a href=\"/wiki/Kandahar\" title=\"Kandahar\">Kandahar<\/a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Ahmad_Shah_Durrani\" title=\"Ahmad Shah Durrani\">Ahmad\nShah Durrani<\/a> established the <a href=\"/wiki/Durrani_Empire\" title=\"Durrani Empire\">Durrani Empire<\/a> in 1747.<sup class=\"reference\" id=\"cite_ref-Last-Afghan-empire_3-1\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Last-Afghan-empire-3\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup class=\"reference\" id=\"cite_ref-14\"><a